3
00:00:12,041 --> 00:00:16,041
<i>"Green onions"
by Booker T. and The MG's.</i>

4
00:00:18,060 --> 00:00:21,520
Aw, come on. Of all the shots,
you leave me with cross side.

5
00:00:21,640 --> 00:00:23,170
I'm screwed.

6
00:00:23,480 --> 00:00:26,220
You know, so-called
experts stroll in here,

7
00:00:26,300 --> 00:00:29,680
"Hey, angle this, angle that."
Blah, blah, blah.

8
00:00:29,740 --> 00:00:32,100
You know what pool is
most of the time ?

9
00:00:32,200 --> 00:00:33,600
Luck.

10
00:00:34,620 --> 00:00:36,460
And I definitely don't have it !

11
00:00:36,510 --> 00:00:38,300
Thanks a lot, cue ball.
I don't need to win.

12
00:00:38,370 --> 00:00:40,840
Why don't you lay smack
next to the eight there ?

13
00:00:42,730 --> 00:00:44,780
Right where you want him, Duke.

14
00:00:51,300 --> 00:00:53,750
Would you look at that ?
Boy, oh, boy.

15
00:00:53,820 --> 00:00:57,360
Bartender, couple shots of Jack
for me and the hustler over here.

16
00:00:57,470 --> 00:00:58,930
Come on. Let's roll again.

17
00:00:59,010 --> 00:01:01,190
What do you say, $75 ?

18
00:01:05,320 --> 00:01:06,680
$150 for the rack ?

19
00:01:06,750 --> 00:01:08,900
$150 ? Oh, I don't know.

20
00:01:09,020 --> 00:01:10,700
All right, forget it.

21
00:01:11,320 --> 00:01:12,740
You know what ? Why not ?

22
00:01:12,840 --> 00:01:14,800
I'm feeling lucky,
like you said.

23
00:01:15,710 --> 00:01:17,300
Oh, by the way,

24
00:01:17,390 --> 00:01:20,970
let me introduce myself.
I'm the Duke.

25
00:01:25,050 --> 00:01:27,250
I know who you are.

26
00:01:30,560 --> 00:01:32,530
So many to choose from.

27
00:01:32,660 --> 00:01:34,390
Corner.

28
00:01:36,890 --> 00:01:37,980
Side.

29
00:01:39,340 --> 00:01:41,350
What the hell, cross bank ?

30
00:01:44,270 --> 00:01:46,770
I am just so damn lucky.

31
00:01:46,880 --> 00:01:48,300
By the way, Duke,

32
00:01:48,360 --> 00:01:50,020
my name's Patrick Lennox.

33
00:01:50,120 --> 00:01:52,160
And you can tell all
the other yuks in Mayberry

34
00:01:52,161 --> 00:01:54,261
that they gotta come see
the Rifle.

35
00:01:54,350 --> 00:01:56,970
Shoots fast, never misses.

36
00:01:59,480 --> 00:02:01,360
Think you're top dog
at the table, do you ?

37
00:02:01,440 --> 00:02:02,630
Yes, ma'am, I do.

38
00:02:02,750 --> 00:02:05,390
The great Baltimore Red's
got nothing on me.

39
00:02:05,520 --> 00:02:07,340
I'd get going, I was you.

40
00:02:10,310 --> 00:02:14,180
My friends, I bid you adieu.

41
00:02:24,630 --> 00:02:26,810
<i>As we told you a moment ago,</i>

42
00:02:26,890 --> 00:02:31,700
<i>President Kennedy was assassinated
in Dallas, Texas today.</i>

43
00:02:31,830 --> 00:02:35,620
<i>He was shot at 12:25</i>

44
00:02:35,800 --> 00:02:39,670
<i>as his car proceed through
the crowded streets of Dallas.</i>

45
00:02:40,110 --> 00:02:44,660
<i>From John John to his father :
a last salute.</i>

46
00:02:55,240 --> 00:02:56,600
Gamblers with sticks,

47
00:02:56,760 --> 00:02:58,800
it's a dangerous combination.

48
00:02:59,180 --> 00:03:01,840
New owner's got evidence
on a Patrick Lennox,

49
00:03:01,940 --> 00:03:04,440
a pool hustler, killed
the same day as Kennedy.

50
00:03:04,510 --> 00:03:05,970
Lennox was known as
"The Rifle."

51
00:03:05,971 --> 00:03:09,471
Cut down before getting his picture
on Whitey's wall of fame.

52
00:03:09,530 --> 00:03:11,320
Gonna see
your mug up here, Boss ?

53
00:03:11,380 --> 00:03:14,280
Don't I wish. Fats, Wimpy Lassiter...
Back in the day,

54
00:03:14,380 --> 00:03:18,300
Whitey's was famous for pool,
gambling, and police raids.

55
00:03:18,940 --> 00:03:20,420
Who's that ?

56
00:03:20,510 --> 00:03:21,620
It's Baltimore Red.

57
00:03:21,770 --> 00:03:23,760
Any of 'em have real names ?

58
00:03:23,810 --> 00:03:27,250
Legend was he'd run 15 racks
in Hoboken,

59
00:03:27,251 --> 00:03:28,851
then do it in Skokie a day later.

60
00:03:28,920 --> 00:03:30,910
Nobody knew where he was from,
who he was.

61
00:03:30,911 --> 00:03:31,811
Real mystery man.

62
00:03:31,890 --> 00:03:33,450
They say Lennox was supposed
to play him

63
00:03:33,451 --> 00:03:35,651
right here at Whitey's night
before he died,

64
00:03:35,740 --> 00:03:37,150
but neither of 'em showed.

65
00:03:37,200 --> 00:03:38,820
Scotty, Lil, Tom Puckett.

66
00:03:38,910 --> 00:03:40,530
He's bringing Whitey's
back to life.

67
00:03:40,620 --> 00:03:41,690
Open next week.

68
00:03:41,691 --> 00:03:43,691
That's, of course, if my liquor license
comes through...

69
00:03:43,760 --> 00:03:45,610
Let's see what you got first, buddy.

70
00:03:45,720 --> 00:03:47,740
Found it shoved way back
in a cue holder

71
00:03:47,820 --> 00:03:50,990
When I saw the date on the newspaper
it was wrapped in, I figured...

72
00:03:51,890 --> 00:03:53,710
.32 snub nose.

73
00:03:53,790 --> 00:03:54,890
Excuse me for a second.

74
00:03:54,990 --> 00:03:56,670
ME report says this "Rifle"

75
00:03:56,671 --> 00:03:58,771
was killed with a.32.
One shot.

76
00:03:58,940 --> 00:04:00,570
Got a spent casing.

77
00:04:00,680 --> 00:04:01,970
Fired once.

78
00:04:02,060 --> 00:04:05,950
"Kennedy Shot In Dallas,
November 22, 1963."

79
00:04:06,150 --> 00:04:09,300
Papers ran five or six extra
editions the day of the assassination.

80
00:04:09,380 --> 00:04:11,580
This one went out at 3:00 p.m.

81
00:04:11,630 --> 00:04:15,290
It matches up.ME listed time
of death approximately 2:00 P.M.

82
00:04:15,380 --> 00:04:17,150
He was killed in Chestnut Hill.

83
00:04:17,220 --> 00:04:20,510
What's a pool hustler
doing over in la-di-da land ?

84
00:04:20,590 --> 00:04:21,920
There's nothing in the file.

85
00:04:21,970 --> 00:04:24,220
Why's no one say squat
about it for 40 years ?

86
00:04:24,260 --> 00:04:27,430
Hustlers and cops, Scotty.
Not exactly bosom buddies.

87
00:04:27,450 --> 00:04:29,660
Maybe the Rifle hustled
the wrong shark ?

88
00:04:29,710 --> 00:04:31,580
And it earned him a bullet.

